# Panzanella

Based on [https://www.themediterraneandish.com/…](https://www.themediterraneandish.com/tomato-panzanella-salad-recipe/#wprm-recipe-container-34832) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20251111231318/https://www.themediterraneandish.com/tomato-panzanella-salad-recipe/))

{ rating="5" image="panzanella.jpeg" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] Rustic Baguette or 1/2 loaf Italian bread or Ciabatta, cut into 1” cubes
- [ ] 1.5 lbs tomatoes, cubed
- [ ] Salt and Pepper
- [ ] 1/8 cup Extra virgin olive oil
- [ ] 1/8 cup red wine vinegar
- [ ] 1/4 tsp Dijon mustard
- [ ] 1 tsp Dried Thyme
- [ ] 1 tsp Dried Basil or 1/2 cup fresh
- [ ] 2 garlic cloves, minced
- [ ] 4 oz fresh baby mozzarella
- [ ] (Optional) 2 Shallots, peeled and thinly sliced
- [ ] (Optional) 1 cup white beans, such as Peruvian or Navy
- [ ] (Optional) Spinach

## Recipe

1. Toast the bread: Pre-heat oven to 400F

   1. In a large mixing bowl, toss the bread cubes, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 tsp thyme, and a generous drizzle of olive oil. Save the bowl
   1. Spread bread cubes on a sheet pan in a single layer. Bake for 10 min until golden and crispy, then let cool
1. Prepare tomatoes: In a colander over the large bowl, toss the tomatoes with 1 tsp salt, 1 tsp basil, and 1 tsp thyme. Allow to drain for a few minutes to release juices
1. Make dressing: Set the colander aside. With the tomato juice in the bowl, add the red wine vinegar, olive oil, dijon mustard, 1 tsp thyme, 1 tsp basil, garlic cloves, and black pepper. Whisk to combine
1. Assemble: In the bowl, combine toasted bread, tomatoes, mozzarella, optional shallots, beans, and spinach. Pour dressing over and toss to coat. Let sit for 20-30 minutes to allow bread to absorb flavors

## Notes

1. Best served within 1-2 hours to maintain some bread texture. For longer storage, keep bread separate until serving
1. For extra flavor: Add capers, kalamata olives, or anchovies
1. Healthier option: Use whole grain bread and add more greens like arugula or spinach
1. Serves 4-6 as a side dish
